args: Say, do you have a minute?\nI could use some advice.
Of course, Luca. What's on your mind?
Sarisse has been acting strangely of late.
She's been conditioning her ears with a\ntrendy, high-end herbal oil.
Hmm. I'm afraid ear conditioning is a bit\noutside my wheelhouse.
But is there really anything wrong with\nsomeone wanting to make themselves\nlook nice?
There is if it's Sarisse! She's never cared\none whit for fashion.
And that's not the only thing that's odd.
She's started going into town a lot more.\n...Alone.
And when I ask what she's been up to,\nshe always changes the subject.\nThis is strange, right?
Perhaps you're being a bit overprotective.
*sigh* I'm overthinking things. I get it.
But she's my little sister, so I can't help\nbut worry.
That's why I wanted your help.\nNow then, here's the plan...
Easy, Luca. If you stick your head out too\nfar, she'll see us.
She's certainly in a fine mood.
...What's this? She's meeting a guy at the\ncosmetics store?
I just couldn't wait! So I was thinking that\ntoday maybe we could, um...
Now close your eyes and pucker up.
Right here? In full view of everyone?\nOh, how embarrassing...
But all right. Just be gentle.
What is she doing? What are THEY doing?!
If she locks lips with a strange man,\nI'll march right in there and—
Easy, Luca! She's not the type to just\nrandomly walk up and kiss some stranger.
That does NOT make me feel better!
But if she's finally grown up, I suppose I\nhave to accept it. She's her own woman,\nand I should be happy she's happy.
...What's that look for? I'm not crying.\nIt's just humid. There's dust everywhere.\nSomeone is chopping onions.
*sniff* It's the end of an era.
We'll make a feast of it tonight. You can\ndrown your sorrows in good food and drink.
Hey, am I invited? Follow-up question:\nWhy are you chuckleheads hiding here?
I noticed you a loooong ways back.\nYou're not terribly subtle.
So then! What brings you here?
He was worried about you, Sarisse.
So we, uh...sort of followed you?
Run to him, Sister! If he is the one,\nthen run to him and never look back!\nI will find my happiness in your own!
Did you eat some strange berries again?
That guy's the shop owner. I shop there.
Sarisse has been helping me try out some\nnew products.
Today I wanted her opinion on lip gloss.
...Lip gloss? Oh. OOOH!\nTHAT'S what it was!
But then why all the secrecy?
We both know you'd tease me if I told you\nI was trying on makeup.
I suppose you're not wrong. ...Heh.\nHa ha ha ha!
Besides, my standards for boyfriend\nmaterial are astronomical.
Not like I've got time to date anyway,\nconsidering that cleaning up after my\nbrother's messes is a full-time job.
You would rather spend time with me?\nHow sweet.
That's not what I meant and you know it!\nHAAAH!
Hrngf?! Ow! Why'd you hit me?
Well, at least now you don't have to worry\nabout her anymore.
